{"title":"The Valley Nis","author":{"name":"Edgar Allan Poe"},"publishDate":"2008-01-28","lines":[{"line":"Far away — far away —","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"Far away — as far at least","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"Lies that valley as the day","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"Down within the golden east —","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"All things lovely — are not they","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"Far away — far away ?","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"It is called the valley Nis.","stanza":2,"number":7},{"line":"And a Syriac tale there is","stanza":2,"number":8},{"line":"Thereabout which Time hath said","stanza":2,"number":9},{"line":"Shall not be interpreted.","stanza":2,"number":10},{"line":"Something about Satan’s dart —","stanza":2,"number":11},{"line":"Something about angel wings —","stanza":2,"number":12},{"line":"Much about a broken heart —","stanza":2,"number":13},{"line":"All about unhappy things:","stanza":2,"number":14},{"line":"But “the valley Nis” at best","stanza":2,"number":15},{"line":"Means “the valley of unrest.”","stanza":2,"number":16},{"line":"Once it smil’d a silent dell","stanza":3,"number":17},{"line":"Where the people did not dwell,","stanza":3,"number":18},{"line":"Having gone unto the wars —","stanza":3,"number":19},{"line":"And the sly, mysterious stars,","stanza":3,"number":20},{"line":"With a visage full of meaning,","stanza":3,"number":21},{"line":"O’er the unguarded flowers were leaning:","stanza":3,"number":22},{"line":"Or the sun ray dripp’d all red","stanza":3,"number":23},{"line":"Thro’ the tulips overhead,","stanza":3,"number":24},{"line":"Then grew paler as it fell","stanza":3,"number":25},{"line":"On the quiet Asphodel.","stanza":3,"number":26},{"line":"Now the unhappy shall confess","stanza":4,"number":27},{"line":"Nothing there is motionless:","stanza":4,"number":28},{"line":"Helen, like thy human eye","stanza":4,"number":29},{"line":"There th’ uneasy violets lie —","stanza":4,"number":30},{"line":"There the reedy grass doth wave","stanza":4,"number":31},{"line":"Over the old forgotten grave —","stanza":4,"number":32},{"line":"One by one from the tree top","stanza":4,"number":33},{"line":"There the eternal dews do drop —","stanza":4,"number":34},{"line":"There the vague and dreamy trees","stanza":4,"number":35},{"line":"Do roll like seas in northern breeze","stanza":5,"number":36},{"line":"Around the stormy Hebrides —","stanza":5,"number":37},{"line":"There the gorgeous clouds do fly,","stanza":5,"number":38},{"line":"Rustling everlastingly,","stanza":5,"number":39},{"line":"Through the terror-stricken sky,","stanza":5,"number":40},{"line":"Rolling like a waterfall","stanza":5,"number":41},{"line":"O’er th’ horizon’s fiery wall —","stanza":5,"number":42},{"line":"There the moon doth shine by night","stanza":5,"number":43},{"line":"With a most unsteady light —","stanza":5,"number":44},{"line":"There the sun doth reel by day","stanza":5,"number":45},{"line":"“Over the hills and far away.”","stanza":5,"number":46}]}